               <p>2172. <persName id="def1-2172-18451027" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-2172-18451027" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2172-18451027" type="surname" value="ROWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2172-18451027" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">DAVID ROWELL</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18451027-2172-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18451027-2172-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18451027-2172-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> for stealing 1 loaf of bread, value 5<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. the goods of <persName id="t18451027-name-1236" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1236" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1236" type="surname" value="ROWLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1236" type="given" value="JONAS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18451027-2172-offence-1 t18451027-name-1236"></join>Jonas Rowley</persName>, his master, since deceased.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1237" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1237" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1237" type="surname" value="ROWLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1237" type="given" value="EMILY REBECCA"></interp>EMILY REBECCA ROWLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I resided with my father, Jonas Rowley—he was a baker—I have been accustomed to transact his business—the prisoner was in his employ—I kept an account of what the prisoner deli<lb></lb>vered to Mrs. Freeman—I got the account from the prisoner—I copied it in the waste book, and then it was copied in the day-book—on the 7th of June the prisoner had one quartern loaf for Mrs. Freeman—it used not to be paid for—it was booked—he ought to have delivered that one loaf and he did not.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HUDDLESTON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You only recollect it from the entry in the book? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I made the entry in the waste book—my father used to copy it in the ledger, and it is in the ledger now—it is from seeing it in the book that I know I gave it him on the 7th of June—I could not charge my memory with it—the waste books were always de<lb></lb>stroyed as soon as they were filled up and entered in the ledger—I made a great many entries in a day—the account used to be given to me after the prisoner had taken the bread—Mrs. Freeman only had bread twice a week—I went before the Magistrate on this case on the 25th of August—nobody served in my father's shop but him and me—my mother was con<lb></lb>fined.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Are you able from recollection to say you gave him this one loaf on the 7th of June? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—Mrs. Freeman had her loaves on Tuesdays and Saturdays—I am able to state that I did, on Saturday the 7th of June, give the prisoner one loaf for her—I never compared the day-book with the waste book, but I can, from my own memory, state I gave him one loaf for her on the 7th of June.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1238" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1238" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1238" type="surname" value="FREEMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1238" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN FREEMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I dealt with Mr. Rowley for bread—I am sure the</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184510270202"></xptr>
               <p>prisoner did not bring me any bread on the 7th of June, because when he did I put it down on a slate.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18451027-2172-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-2172-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-2172-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value=""></interp>NOT GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>.</p>
               <p>(There were three other charges against the prisoner, on which no evidence was offered.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Before Mr. Recorder.</hi>
